snippet: The Commerce Department reported that groundbreaking rose 10.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.17 million units last month.
abstract: Commerce Dept says housing starts in November rose 10.5 percent to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.17 million units; building permits rise 11 percent to 1.29 million-unit rate.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department reported that groundbreaking rose 10.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.17 million units last month.

headline.main: Housing Starts Rebound and Building Permits Hit 5-Month High
headline.print_headline: Housing Starts Rebound and Building Permits Soar
